Executive Profile
John Wendell Thompson  Advisor, PernixData, IncAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 13 different industries.See Board Relationships68--
Background

		Mr. John Wendell Thompson serves as an Advisor of PernixData, Inc. Mr. Thompson serves as the President of Junction Engineering Ltd. He serves as Strategic Advisor of Contrast Security, Inc. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at Virtual Instruments Corporation from May 2010 to April 7, 2016. He joined Virtual Instruments as an investor in 2009. He served as the President of Symantec Corporation from April 1999 to January 2002 and served as its Chief Executive Officer ... from April 1999 to April 2009. Mr. Thompson served as the Chief Executive Officer of Veritas Software Corp. He had a distinguished career with the International Business Machines Corporation. He worked for 28 years at International Business Machines Corporation, where he held a number of leadership positions, including sales, marketing, software development. He served as General Manager of IBM Americas at International Business Machines Corporation. He has 28 years of prior leadership experience at IBM. He has been the Independent Chairman of Microsoft Corporation since February 4, 2014. He served as the Chairman of Veritas Software Corp. He served as the Chairman of Symantec Corporation since April 1999. He has been an Independent Director of Microsoft Corporation since February 20, 2012 and served as its Lead Independent Director from November 2012 to February 4, 2014. He has been a Director of Illumio, Inc. since November 10, 2014 and Illumina, Inc. May 3, 2017. Mr. Thompson served as a Director of Virtual Instruments Corporation from October 2009 to April 7, 2016. He served as a Director of Veritas Software Technology Corporation since November 2000. He serves as a Director of Liquid Robotics. He serves as a Director of Domo Technologies, Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of ECL Group of Companies Ltd. He served as an Independent Director of United Parcel Service, Inc. from 2000 to May 2, 2013. He served as a Director of Seagate Technology Public Limited Company from November 2000 to October 26, 2011. He served as a Director of Crystal Decisions Inc. since February 2001 and Northern Indiana Public Service Company, Inc. since 1993. He served as a Director of JovianDATA. Mr. Thompson served as a Member of Advisory Board of ITM Software Corp. He served as a Director of Teach For America, Inc., Veritas Software Corp., Seagate Software (Cayman) Holdings Corporation. He served as a Director of NiSource Inc. from 1993 to August 24, 2005 and Symantec Corporation from 1999 to 2011. Since 2009, he has been an active investor in early-stage technology companies in Silicon Valley. In September 2002, President George W. Bush appointed Mr. Thompson to the National Infrastructure Advisory Committee (NIAC). He serves as the Chairman of the Silicon Valley Blue Ribbon Task Force on Aviation Security and Technology. He was a member of IBM's Worldwide Management Council. In May 2008, he received an Honorary Doctorate Degree from Notre Dame University. Mr. Thompson holds a Master's Degree in Management Science from MIT’s Sloan School of Management and BA Degree in Business Administration from Florida A&M University.Read Full Background




