Insider Activity


Individual




John Wendell Thompson



Dr. John W. Thompson is Independent Chairman at Microsoft Corp. and Chief Executive Officer & Director at Virtual Instruments Corp. He  is on the Board of Directors at Virtual Instruments Corp., Illumio, Inc., JovianDATA, Inc. and Liquid Robotics, Inc. 
Dr. Thompson was previously employed as Independent Director by United Parcel Service, Inc., General Manager by International Business Machines Corp., Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Symantec Corp., and a Trustee by Wetlands America Trust, Inc. He also served on the board at Seagate Technology Plc, Beam Suntory, Inc., Crystal Decisions, Inc., Domo, Inc., NiSource, Inc., Northern Indiana Public Service Co., Seagate Technology LLC and Teach For America, Inc. 
He received his undergraduate degree from Florida A&M University and a graduate degree from MIT Sloan School of Management.



