A group representing major technology companies has aligned itself against Qualcomm Inc (QCOM) in its legal dispute with Apple Inc (AAPL) by calling on regulators to reject Qualcomm's (QCOM) bid to ban the import of iPhones. A lobbying group that represents Alphabet Inc's Google, Amazon.com Inc (AMZN), Microsoft Corp (MSFT) and Facebook Inc (FB) filed comments with the U.S. International Trade Commission.

















